Key Components in Simulator Data System:

Simulator Data Generator

Generates synthetic data (positions, speeds, altitudes, etc.).

Data Processor

Processes the generated data for validity and formatting.

Data Repository

Stores both real and simulated data.

Data Dispatcher

Sends data (simulated or real) to other system components or clients.

Client Interface

Receives and displays flight data (map visualizer, dashboards).

Simulator Controller

Manages simulation scenarios (start, stop, adjust parameters).

Logging & Monitoring

Logs simulator data activity and monitors system health.

Component Diagram (textual representation):
+------------------------+
| Simulator Controller    |
| - manages simulation    |
+-----------+------------+
            |                                            
            v
+------------------------+
| Simulator Data Generator|<----------------+
| - creates synthetic data|                 |
+-----------+------------+                  |
            |                               |
            v                               |
+------------------------+                  |
| Data Processor  |                  |
| - validates and formats|                  |
+-----------+------------+                  |
            |                               |
            v                               |
+------------------------+                  |
| Data Repository  |<----------------+
| - stores real & simulated data            |
+-----------+------------+
            |
            v
+------------------------+
| Data Dispatcher        |
| - distributes data to  |
|   clients & systems    |
+-----------+------------+
            |
            v
+------------------------+
| Client Interface       |
| - visualizes data      |
+------------------------+

+------------------------+
| Logging & Monitoring   |
| - logs & monitors data |
+------------------------+

Explanation:

The Simulator Controller commands the data generator to produce simulated.

The Simulator Data Generator creates data which is then processed by the Data Processor.

The processed data is stored in the Data Repository.

The Data Dispatcher sends this data to the Client Interface for visualization.

Throughout, the Logging & Monitoring component tracks system behavior.
